## Laravel Setup Instructions

### Step 1: Create Mailable Classes

```bash
php artisan make:mail ApplicationConfirmation
php artisan make:mail AdminNewApplication
php artisan make:mail InterviewScheduled
php artisan make:mail ApplicationStatusUpdate
php artisan make:mail AdminJobPosted
php artisan make:mail RejectionEmail
php artisan make:mail OfferLetter
```

### Step 2: Update Mailable Classes

**Example: `app/Mail/ApplicationConfirmation.php`**

```php
<?php

namespace App\Mail;

use Illuminate\Bus\Queueable;
use Illuminate\Mail\Mailable;
use Illuminate\Mail\Mailables\Content;
use Illuminate\Mail\Mailables\Envelope;

class ApplicationConfirmation extends Mailable
{
    use Queueable;

    public function __construct(
        public array $candidate,
        public string $position,
        public string $appliedDate,
        public string $applicationId,
        public string $trackingLink
    ) {}

    public function envelope(): Envelope
    {
        return new Envelope(
            subject: 'Application Confirmation - ' . $this->position,
        );
    }

    public function content(): Content
    {
        return new Content(
            view: 'emails.application-confirmation',
        );
    }
}
```

### Step 3: Send Emails in Controller

```php
use App\Mail\ApplicationConfirmation;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Mail;

public function submit(Request $request)
{
    // Validate and save application...
    
    $candidate = [
        'fullName' => $request->fullName,
        'email' => $request->email,
        'phoneNumber' => $request->phoneNumber,
    ];
    
    // Send confirmation to candidate
    Mail::to($candidate['email'])->send(new ApplicationConfirmation(
        $candidate,
        $request->serviceType,
        now()->format('M d, Y'),
        'APP-' . uniqid(),
        route('candidate.track-application')
    ));
    
    // Send notification to admin
    Mail::to(config('mail.admin_email'))->send(new AdminNewApplication(
        $candidate,
        $request->serviceType,
        now()->format('M d, Y'),
        route('admin.applications')
    ));
    
    return response()->json(['success' => true]);
}
```

### Step 4: Configure `.env`

```env
MAIL_DRIVER=smtp
MAIL_HOST=smtp.mailtrap.io
MAIL_PORT=587
MAIL_USERNAME=your_username
MAIL_PASSWORD=your_password
MAIL_FROM_ADDRESS=noreply@jobsystem.com
MAIL_FROM_NAME="Job Management System"
```

