## Testing Emails Locally

Use **Mailtrap** or **MailHog** for local testing:

```bash
# Using tinker to test
php artisan tinker

Mail::to('test@example.com')->send(
    new \App\Mail\ApplicationConfirmation(
        ['fullName' => 'John Doe', 'email' => 'john@example.com', 'phoneNumber' => '123456789'],
        'React Developer',
        now()->format('M d, Y'),
        'APP-123',
        'http://localhost/track'
    )
);
```

---

## Customization Tips

- Update colors in the templates to match your brand
- Add your company logo in the header
- Include social media links in the footer
- Customize the CTA button text and colors
- Add legal disclaimers as needed

